From 4590caf67ab7de99e7a1ea2bc70d2429b5f855e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Mahalingam <bmahalin@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 30 May 2025 22:20:41 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 01/11] QSDK:DP:wifi: Add support for PPE-DS(Direct switch)
 feature in the Unified Driver

This adds support for the PPE-DS feature in the Unified Driver and the below
aspects are covered in this patchset
        1. PPE-DS Ring Buffer Init/Deinit
        2. Buffer Transmit and Transmit Completion
        3. Buffer Reception and Replenish
        4. PPE-VP Table entries management
        5. VP(Virtual Port) init/deinit and registration
        6. WBM Configuration for completion
        7. Interrupt registration and management
        8. Interrupt grouping for PPE-DS rings.
        9. HAL API for PPE-DS ring management
        10. Support for QCN9274 PPE-DS feature
        11. RxOLE config to deliver special frames in Host path.
        12. FSE support to use PPE

Patch-dependency:
        0134-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-support-for-WDS-Ext.patch
        0132-0001-QSDK-wifi-ath12k-Add-ECM-Callback-changes-for-FST-fe.patch
        0132-0013-QSDK-wifi-ath12k-Integrate-dp-FST-APIs-in-ECM-Change.patch
Patch-work: None

